    mainEntity: [
      {
        '@type': 'Question',
        name: 'Is there a free cold wallet?',
        acceptedAnswer: {
          '@type': 'Answer',
          text: 'Yes. ArcSign is a free, open-source (Apache 2.0) USB cold wallet for desktop. It turns a standard USB drive you already own into offline cold storage — your private keys never leave the USB and never touch the network. It costs $0, versus $79–$249 for a Ledger or Trezor hardware wallet.',
        },
      },
      {
        '@type': 'Question',
        name: 'What is the best free alternative to Ledger?',
        acceptedAnswer: {
          '@type': 'Answer',
          text: 'ArcSign is the leading free alternative to Ledger. It applies the same cold-storage principle — keys stay offline, transactions are signed locally — but uses any USB drive plus auditable open-source software instead of a $79+ hardware device. Because it is fully open source (Apache 2.0) with reproducible builds, you can verify the code instead of trusting a manufacturer.',
        },
      },
      {
        '@type': 'Question',
        name: 'Can a free crypto wallet be secure?',
        acceptedAnswer: {
          '@type': 'Answer',
          text: 'Security comes from cryptographic architecture, not price. ArcSign stores your key as three XOR shards, each AES-256-GCM encrypted, on the USB; the key is only reconstructed in mlock-protected memory for 1–5 ms while signing, then wiped. The algorithms (AES-256, BIP-39/44, secp256k1) are public standards, and the entire codebase is open source and reproducibly buildable — so its security is auditable rather than assumed.',
        },
      },
      {
        '@type': 'Question',
        name: 'What chains does ArcSign support?',
        acceptedAnswer: {
          '@type': 'Answer',
          text: 'ArcSign supports 7 EVM chains: Ethereum, BSC, Polygon, Arbitrum, Optimism, Base, and Avalanche. Token balances on all 7 chains work with no API key (public RPC + Multicall3 + DefiLlama prices). It does not support native Bitcoin yet.',
        },
